                            <comment id="15213019" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Sat, 26 Mar 2016 13:19:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jim, I see nothing in the section 3.3.4 that the unmapped exceptions should have the causes checked for WebApplicationException (have a look please), looks like it is RI specific, but the change seems all right, the systests are OK.&lt;br/&gt;
I did a minor update to make sure that if the response has CT then it is made immediately available to the exchange&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15213911" author="ema" created="Mon, 28 Mar 2016 07:25:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Sergey, There is similar item defined in jaxrs 1.1 6.3  to unwrap an EJBException. I think it&apos;s no harm to unwrap an exception other than EJBException if the nested exception is WAE.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15217750" author="sergey_beryozkin" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2016 09:53:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sure, can you please merge to 3.1.x and also 3.0.x ? Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
